    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Features are extracted from mzML fragmentation files using the pymzML library and stored in a relational database (PostgreSQL) alongside inferred Mass2Motifs and associated metadata... fragment and neutral loss features are extracted from the uploaded fragmentation file [mzML (alongside an optional peaklist file to filter the extracted precursors, see Supplementary Section S1), MSP, or MGF formats]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MS2LDA accepts .mgf, .msp, .mzML formats and extracts fragment/neutral loss features, but does not explicitly describe the conversion to 'bag-of-fragments' representation or LDA training pipeline. The paper focuses on MS2LDA as a topic-modelling method (analogous to LDA) but does not detail the intermediate preprocessing steps or corpus format generation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx582",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does MS2LDA convert mass spectrometry input files in multiple formats (.mgf, .msp, .mzML) into a bag-of-fragments representation suitable for LDA training?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:51:05.638516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not describe the output format of preprocessing or corpus generation. It mentions features are 'stored in a relational database (PostgreSQL)' but does not specify document-term matrix, serialized Python objects, or LDA-compatible formats.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx582",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Bag-of-fragments corpus in LDA-compatible format (document-term matrix or serialized Python object)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:51:05.638516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "fragment and neutral loss features are extracted from the uploaded fragmentation file... MS2LDA is performed on the loaded spectra, and the results are stored in the database",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms extraction of 'fragment and neutral loss features' but does not explicitly describe a 'token inventory' or 'mass-to-token mappings' as a discrete output artifact.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx582",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Fragment and neutral loss token inventory with mass-to-token mappings",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:51:05.638516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Various filtering options are provided to allow for filtering of the loaded spectra, and the user can also specify algorithm properties (number of Mass2Motifs and number of algorithm iterations).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper mentions filtering options are available but does not describe a 'quality control report' as an explicit output or document filtering statistics and retained fragment counts.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx582",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Quality control report documenting noise filtering statistics and retained fragment counts",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:51:05.638516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
