    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as 'reconstructing the LDA model training step' and focuses on model artifacts and convergence visualization. The paper is primarily a software/web application paper describing ms2lda.org, a user-facing platform for MS2LDA analysis. The paper does not detail the internal training algorithm, convergence criteria, or model serialization formats.",
        "The expected outputs (binary model file, JSON motif set, convergence curve) are implementation-specific details not discussed in the paper. The paper emphasizes database storage and interactive web visualizations rather than file-based model artifacts.",
        "The card's framing suggests a machine-learning model training task, whereas the paper presents MS2LDA as an already-developed method being deployed as a web service with user-friendly workflows."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
