    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_003/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We recently published MS2LDA, a method for the decomposition of sets of molecular fragment data derived from large metabolomics experiments. To make the method more widely available to the community, here we present ms2lda.org, a web application that allows users to upload their data, run MS2LDA analyses and explore the results through interactive visualizations.",
      "asbval:note": "MS2LDA is the core method described throughout the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx582",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MS2LDA",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:51:58.097665+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_003/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Ms2lda.org also includes a growing library of pre-annotated Mass2Motifs from the Massbank and GNPS data sets (van der Hooft et al., 2016) for matching and decomposition. As a new feature, we offer matching functionality which allows users to compare the Mass2Motifs found in their data with those in our growing database of (often annotated) Mass2Motifs.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes annotation records and matching functionality for Mass2Motifs, but does not specify JSON format, Spec2Vec similarity scores, or confidence metrics. The annotation mechanism is matching against pre-annotated Mass2Motifs from MassBank and GNPS, not Spec2Vec-based scoring.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx582",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Per-motif annotation records in JSON format with motif identifiers, suggested structure labels, Spec2Vec similarity scores, and confidence metrics",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T21:51:58.097665+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_5281_zenodo_15858124__task_003/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card describes a Spec2Vec-based automated annotation process (MAG), which is not present in the paper. The paper's actual annotation approach relies on manual inspection, database matching against MassBank/GNPS, and user-driven annotation transfer.",
        "The research question and title focus on Spec2Vec and MAG, neither of which are mentioned in the paper. This represents significant scope drift from the paper's actual content.",
        "The paper is about ms2lda.org, a web application for MS2LDA analysis and visualization, not about a Spec2Vec-based annotation guidance system."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
