    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragment-ion-peak-detection-and-normalization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Features are extracted from mzML fragmentation files using the pymzML library and stored in a relational database (PostgreSQL) alongside inferred Mass2Motifs and associated metadata.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes feature extraction from MS/MS data and loading spectra in multiple formats (mzML, MSP, MGF), but does not explicitly describe intensity normalization to a common scale as a preprocessing step. The paper focuses on MS2LDA decomposition (topic modeling) rather than detailed preprocessing workflows. Intensity normalization is implied as part of the MS2LDA method but not explicitly documented in these passages.",
