      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MS2LDA, a method inspired by text modelling, to decompose fragmentation spectra into sets of conserved fragment and neutral loss features (called Mass2Motifs). As text documents can be decomposed into sets of co-occurring words (topics) MS2LDA decomposes each molecule into sets of Mass2Motifs",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes MS2LDA as inspired by text modelling and topic decomposition, which is semantically equivalent to Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA). The analogy to topic modeling confirms LDA as the underlying algorithm.",
