    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/neutral-loss-composition-matching/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Ms2lda.org also includes a growing library of pre-annotated Mass2Motifs from the Massbank and GNPS data sets (van der Hooft et al., 2016) for matching and decomposition. As a new feature, we offer matching functionality which allows users to compare the Mass2Motifs found in their data with those in our growing database of (often annotated) Mass2Motifs.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes matching Mass2Motifs against a database of pre-annotated motifs from Massbank and GNPS, but does NOT mention MassQL or MotifDB by name. The matching functionality exists but uses Massbank/GNPS, not the specific 'MotifDB' or 'MassQL' tools named in the card. The paper does not describe constructing MassQL queries or ranking by similarity score explicitly.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1093-bioinformatics-btx582",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
