      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Ms2lda.org allows users to decompose and annotate MS/MS data with MS2LDA... we provide a new visualization screen, the ability to store annotations, decomposition, motif matching and MS1 analysis... The starting point for visualization is the network graph (A), nodes represent Mass2Motifs (circle) and molecules (squares)... Edges represent connections between molecules and Mass2Motifs (above a certain threshold).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes network visualization with edges representing connections between molecules and Mass2Motifs, but does not explicitly mention computing pairwise spectral similarity or cosine similarity between Mass2Motif pseudo-spectra. The network construction mechanism is not detailed in provided passages. Matching functionality is mentioned but not described as similarity-based computation.",
